observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a. Municipal GSO to coordinate with the Municipal Engineer to prepare the road map of the Municipality to facilitate the preparation of a proper inventory and reporting of the Municipality’s road network; 
b. Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and thereafter;
c. Municipal Accountant to record the amount of road networks and the equivalent to the required transition provision percentage of road networks every year starting 2016 up to 2019.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the:

a. Inventory Committee to complete the inventory count to prove existence of the Municipality’s properties, and to submit the required report thereon to the Auditor, pursuant to Section 124 of the MNGAS, Volume I. Also, the inventory report should be reconciled with the accounting and property records. Any discrepancies found should be investigated, and the necessary adjustments should be made where the error was committed;

b. OIC-GSO to maintain Property Cards to facilitate the physical count of property and equipment. Determine the officials/employees to whom the equipment were issued, and issue the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) for each property to pinpoint the direct person accountable and responsible thereon. Moreover, renew all ARE every three years for the signature of the holder of each item listed in the RPCPPE;

c. Municipal Accountant to maintain PPELC for each category of PPE to ensure correctness of the control account in the GL; and

d. OIC-GSO to prepare the Inventory and Inspection Report on Unserviceable Property (IIURP), to account for all unserviceable and obsolete items previously taken up in the books as assets, so that they may be properly disposed of and dropped from the accounts. Moreover, the disposal of property shall be made in accordance with COA Circular No. 89-296 dated January 27, 1989.

We also recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting journal entry to correct the provision for depreciation on property amounting to at least P1,024,661.45, for fair presentation of affected PPE accounts in the financial statements.
